abstract: Everton named Carlo Ancelotti, one of Europe's most successful coaches, as their new manager on Saturday, giving the three times Champions League winner a 4-1/2 year contract.
snippet: Everton named Carlo Ancelotti, one of Europe's most successful coaches, as their new manager on Saturday, giving the three times Champions League winner a 4-1/2 year contract.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Everton named Carlo Ancelotti, one of Europe's most successful coaches, as their new manager on Saturday, giving the three times Champions League winner a 4-1/2 year contract.
headline_main: Ancelotti Seals Premier League Return as New Everton Manager
headline_print_headline: Ancelotti Seals Premier League Return as New Everton Manager

abstract: Gunmen opened fire on a small commercial plane as it landed in Indonesia's restive province of Papua carrying nine passengers, one of the plane's pilots said Saturday. No casualties were reported.
snippet: Gunmen opened fire on a small commercial plane as it landed in Indonesia's restive province of Papua carrying nine passengers, one of the plane's pilots said Saturday. No casualties were reported.
lead_paragraph: JAKARTA, Indonesia — Gunmen opened fire on a small commercial plane as it landed in Indonesia's restive province of Papua carrying nine passengers, one of the plane's pilots said Saturday. No casualties were reported.
headline_main: Gunmen Attack Plane in Indonesia's Papua; No Casualties
headline_print_headline: Gunmen Attack Plane in Indonesia's Papua; No Casualties

abstract: Forest Green Rovers, arguably the most talked about English lower-league soccer club due to their green ethos, received an early Christmas present after their plans for a 5,000-seat wooden stadium were finally approved.
snippet: Forest Green Rovers, arguably the most talked about English lower-league soccer club due to their green ethos, received an early Christmas present after their plans for a 5,000-seat wooden stadium were finally approved.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Forest Green Rovers, arguably the most talked about English lower-league soccer club due to their green ethos, received an early Christmas present after their plans for a 5,000-seat wooden stadium were finally approved.
headline_main: Forest Green Score Eco-Friendly Goal After New Stadium Plans Approved
headline_print_headline: Forest Green Score Eco-Friendly Goal After New Stadium Plans Approved

abstract: Pope Francis warned Saturday that "rigidity" in living out the Christian faith is creating a "minefield" of hatred and misunderstanding in a world where Christianity is increasingly irrelevant.
snippet: Pope Francis warned Saturday that "rigidity" in living out the Christian faith is creating a "minefield" of hatred and misunderstanding in a world where Christianity is increasingly irrelevant.
lead_paragraph: VATICAN CITY — Pope Francis warned Saturday that "rigidity" in living out the Christian faith is creating a "minefield" of hatred and misunderstanding in a world where Christianity is increasingly irrelevant.
headline_main: Pope Denounces 'Rigidity' as He Warns of Christian Decline
headline_print_headline: Pope Denounces 'Rigidity' as He Warns of Christian Decline

abstract: Indian authorities have stepped up phone and mobile internet shutdowns in some parts of the country in an effort to thwart a groundswell of protests over a new citizenship law that excludes Muslims.
snippet: Indian authorities have stepped up phone and mobile internet shutdowns in some parts of the country in an effort to thwart a groundswell of protests over a new citizenship law that excludes Muslims.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Indian authorities have stepped up phone and mobile internet shutdowns in some parts of the country in an effort to thwart a groundswell of protests over a new citizenship law that excludes Muslims.
headline_main: India Suspends Internet and Phone Services to Quell Protests
headline_print_headline: India Suspends Internet and Phone Services to Quell Protests

abstract: LA Fresh Poultry, a halal-style butchery, caters to a diverse clientele of home chefs and professionals who want to be reminded of their roots.
snippet: LA Fresh Poultry, a halal-style butchery, caters to a diverse clientele of home chefs and professionals who want to be reminded of their roots.
lead_paragraph: Betty Figueroa, 52, rides the 720 Wilshire rapid bus for more than two hours every morning from her apartment in the Koreatown neighborhood of Los Angeles to her housekeeping job in Brentwood. It takes her another two hours — depending on traffic — to get back to the apartment where she lives with her mother, Deborah Hernández, 80, and her two daughters each afternoon.

abstract: The clothing industry produces tons of fabric that is never sold. FabScrap wants to help.
snippet: The clothing industry produces tons of fabric that is never sold. FabScrap wants to help.
lead_paragraph: Tucked away in the bowels of the Brooklyn Army Terminal is a 4,000-square-foot warehouse filled from wall to wall and floor to ceiling with garbage bags. They contain castoffs from New York’s fashion studios: mock-up pockets ripped from sample jeans, swatches in next season’s paisley print.

abstract: Hong Kong riot police swept into several shopping malls on Saturday, chasing off and arresting some anti-government Hong Kong demonstrators who had gathered to press their demands in the peak shopping weekend before Christmas.

lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Hong Kong riot police swept into several shopping malls on Saturday, chasing off and arresting some anti-government Hong Kong demonstrators who had gathered to press their demands in the peak shopping weekend before Christmas.
headline_main: Hong Kong Protesters Face Off With Police in Mall Protests

abstract: Former Tottenham Hotspur manager Mauricio Pochettino says he is ready to return to management quickly, showing no interest in an extended break from the game.

headline_main: No Sabbatical, Pochettino Says He Is Ready to Return to Management

abstract: A mysterious figure who used a rare narwhal tusk to help subdue a knife-wielding extremist on London Bridge last month has been identified as a civil servant in Britain's Justice Ministry.
